# About Me
- My name is Misha. I prefer concise, direct responses.

# Engineering Principles
- TDD: write a failing test first, then implement, then refactor. No exceptions.
- SOLID principles. DRY. Apply design patterns where they reduce coupling and improve clarity.
- Readable > clever. Meaningful variable names.
- Always add error handling — no happy-path-only code.
- Keep functions short and focused. One responsibility per function/class.

# Git
- Conventional Commits. Feature branches. Squash-merge PRs.
- Never commit secrets. Never push to main directly.

# Testing
- Unit tests: fast, isolated, mock externals. Arrange-Act-Assert.
- Name tests clearly: what, when, expected outcome.
- Test behavior, not implementation details.

# Security
- Validate all input. Parameterized queries only. HTTPS only in production.
- Never log secrets. Never run sudo. Never force-push to main.
